quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  10,43,"And among them there are those who look at you. Would you, then, guide the blind even when they have no insight?"
  10,44,"Surely, Allah does not do wrong to people at all, but the people do wrong to their own selves."
  10,45,"And the Day when He will gather them, (they will feel) like they had not stayed for any longer than a fraction of a day as they will recognize each other. Losers, in-deed, are those who deny that they will ever face Allah, and they are not on the right path."
  10,46,"So, no matter whether We show you some of what We warn them of, or We take you back to Us (before it), in any case, they have to return to Us. Then, Allah is witness to what they do."
  10,47,"And for every people there is a messenger. So, when their messenger comes, the matter will be decided between them with justice, and they shall not be wronged."
  10,48,"And they say, "When will this promise be (fulfilled) if you are true?""
  10,49,"Say, "I have no power to bring a harm or a benefit to myself, except what Allah wills. For every people there is an appointed time. When their time comes, they will not be late for a moment, nor will they be earlier."
  10,50,"Say, "Just tell me, if His punishment befalls you at night or by day, what is there in it that the sinners wish to come soon?"
  10,51,"Is it then when it befalls you that you will believe in it? Now (you believe)? And you have been asking for it to come sooner!""
  10,52,"Then it will be said to the unjust, "Taste the punishment lasting forever. You shall not be punished except for what you have been earning.""
  10,53,"And they want you to tell them whether it is true. Say, "Yes, by my Lord, it is true. And you cannot frustrate (His plan).""